%pyspark

from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import (IntegerType, FloatType, StringType)

udf_dnt2dt = udf(lambda d, t: d + ' ' + t)
udf_uvbr = udf(lambda uva, uvb: uvb/(uva+uvb), FloatType())
udf_uvar = udf(lambda uva, uvb: uva/(uva+uvb), FloatType())

udf_year = udf(lambda date: int(date.split('-')[0]), IntegerType())
udf_month = udf(lambda date: int(date.split('-')[1]), IntegerType())
udf_day = udf(lambda date: int(date.split('-')[2]), IntegerType())
udf_hour = udf(lambda time: int(time.split(':')[0]), IntegerType())
udf_minute = udf(lambda time: int(time.split(':')[1]), IntegerType())

udf_uvi = udf(lambda uvi: int(uvi), IntegerType())

def weather(month):
    if 3 <= month <= 5:
        return '봄'
    elif 6 <= month <= 8:
        return '여름'
    elif 9 <= month <= 11:
        return '가을'
    elif month <= 12 or 1 <= month <= 2:
        return '겨울'
    else:
        return 'NaN'

udf_weather = udf(weather, StringType())

%pyspark

uv_1 = uv.withColumn('uvar', udf_uvar('uva', 'uvb'))\
         .withColumn('uvbr', udf_uvbr('uva', 'uvb'))\
         .withColumn('datetime', udf_dnt2dt('date', 'time'))\
         .withColumn('year', udf_year('date'))\
         .withColumn('month', udf_month('date'))\
         .withColumn('day', udf_day('date'))\
         .withColumn('hour', udf_hour('time'))\
         .withColumn('minute', udf_minute('time'))\
         .withColumn('weather', udf_weather('month'))\
         .withColumn('uvi_i', udf_uvi('uvi'))\
         .sort('datetime')

uv_1.show()
uv_1.createOrReplaceTempView('uv')

%sql
select date, time, uva, uvb, uvbr, weather from uv
-- where weather = '겨울'
